        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "οὐδὲ ἁμαρτία",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", for Paul in chap. 2 recognises the existence and guilt of sin even where men live ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἀνόμως",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; but in comparison with the deliberate and conscious transgression of those who live ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐν νόμῳ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", such sin is comparatively insignificant and venial, and is here left out of account. The alternative systems are reduced to two, Law and Grace (or Promise).",
        "children": []
